snippet.textDisplay: King stud goes from plate to plate, jack holds up the window header, your legs are what holds up the sill and cripples are small blocks you put usually between a header and the top plate. A better way to make headers is to use 2x10 or 2x8 with half inch plywood in the middle to achieve the 5 1/2 inch spacing
